docs.summary:
*
AccountDeletionRequest is the main entity of GdprAutomations that can be used for submitting account deletion requests

members.name: id
members.doc: AccountDeletionRequest ID

members.name: userGuid
members.doc: Represents the id of the user to be deleted

members.name: answersTicketId
members.doc: Represents the id of the corresponding wix answers ticket used to track and manage the request

members.name: createdDate
members.doc: Represents the time this AccountDeletionRequest was created

members.name: status
members.doc: Represents the submission status of the request

members.name: requestError
members.doc: Represents the error state of the request, that should be resolved prior to submission

members.name: emergencyOptOut
members.doc: Represents an explicit admin request to block the request from being submitted for deletion

members.name: harvesterRequestId
members.doc: Represents the id of the corresponding deletion request created by the harvester once this request was submitted to the harvester

members.name: revision
members.doc: Represents the current state of an item. Each time the item is modified, its `revision` changes. for an update operation to succeed, you MUST pass the latest revision

members.name: updatedDate
members.doc: Represents the time this AccountDeletionRequest was last updated

members.name: submissionInformation
members.doc: Represents the submission request information used to create the corresponding wix answers ticket

docs.summary:
*
SubmissionInformation is being used to provide support agents clear visibility about the request via the wix answers ticket
This entity contains PII data which is only being used when opening the wix answers ticket upon an incoming request
This entity is not being saved in the db, nor being returned by the api

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • TICKET_CREATED
  • NOTIFY_USER_REQUEST_CREATED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his deletion request has been created
  • BLOCK_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to block the users account
  • NOTIFY_USER_ACCOUNT_BLOCKED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his account has been blocked
  • ADD_NOTE_TO_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to add a note to users account in the user manager
  • UNBLOCK_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to unblock the users account
  • NOTIFY_USER_ACCOUNT_UNBLOCKED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his account has been unblocked
  • INTERNALLY_NOTIFY_EMERGENCY_OPT_OUT - Represents a failure to internally notify the support agents via wix answers that the account has been successfully opted out

Possible values are:
  • PENDING_CONFIRMATION - Represents a deletion request which has not been confirmed by the user
  • CONFIRMED - Represents a deletion request which has been confirmed by the user
  • CANCELED - Represents a deletion request which was canceled on behalf of the user
  • SUBMITTED - Represents a deletion request which was submitted to the gdpr harvester
  • DONE - Represents a deletion request which was deleted successfully by the gdpr harvester

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • FREE - Represents a free users account
  • PREMIUM - Represents a premium users account - currently not supported by automations service
  • NO_WEBSITE - Represents a no website users account - currently not supported by automations service
